<tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprofxeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>prof xeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 5:34:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> So this grew out of my asking what piercer I should buy... the fungusbeast spine was suggested.  It is 13/28 with a Disease Damage of 2.  Now, I know with the Damage Bonus numbers, those are only tacked on at the end.  So they don't really help us with backstab (or so goes my understanding).  Is the same true with the disease damage above, or does that make this in effect a 15/28?  I'm just trying to understand it all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br><br>Thanks,<br>Xeen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprofxeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>prof xeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 11:35:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Anyone?</span><hr size=1> Still trying to figure this one out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>-Xeen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 11:55:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> Elemental damage is not a damage bonus (nor is bane damage).  It is added directly to the base damage before it goes through the calculation.  <br><br>So, yes, a fungusbeast spine is occasionally 15/28, a LSoEE is occasionally 21/29, and Greenmist is 24/22 against shissar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprofxeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>prof xeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 12:23:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thank you</span><hr size=1> Many thanks!<br><br>-Xeen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uheelan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heelan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 9:01:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thank you</span><hr size=1> Aye, I've had backstabs in the 300+ range with a Fungusbeast Spine with a skill of 179 (skill is 186 now).  And am piercing for a max of 63 now with a skill of 210 and strength at 215 with one shaman strength buff.  So, in conclusion it would definitely appear to add to weapon base damage.  <br><br>Forgot to mention, when they bugged the bane and elemental damage weapons it would appear what they were trying to do was add the extra damage to the weapons base, but they did it a little too well ;)  That was when you had low level rogues backstabbing for 600+ and high level rogues piercing for thousands. <p><BR><BR><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91415">Pokya Bakwitanife</a><BR><BR>Toblinzik Marrowmaster<BR>Necro of the 29th Bone<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uheelan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heelan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/22/02 9:05:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueinthunder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>einThunder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 10:54:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thank you</span><hr size=1> but those damage modifiers can be resisted! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubronusblackblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bronus Blackblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 11:54:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thank you</span><hr size=1> I believe the above is incorrect.  Bane damage gets added to the base of the weapon, elemental damage gets added as a + on the end.  This was based on the absolute max damage of an LSoEE coming nowhere near what it should be if it was truly 21 dmg base. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82998>Bronus Blackblade</a> - Assassin<br><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94791>Mystin De`Vermiis</a> - Enchanter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shamah>Shamah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 12:11:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> heh... ironic that I was just about to post a similar thread.<br><br>i'm just starting to pay attention to this kind of stuff, so this may sound silly, but, if bane dmg goes into effect with BS... what about regular bonus dmg?  I just got a 10 22 weapon with a damage bonus of 4, so does that mean I'm wielding a 14 22 weapon, or a 10 22 with and extra 4 dmg with every attack?<br><br>Thanks for the time <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 1:34:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> The damage bonus is added after, bane and elemental are added before.  Unless you actually have evidence to the contrary, just take my word for it.  I'm not digging out the graphs I made back in December to prove it again...<br><br>(This isn't in the FAQ?  It should be) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubronusblackblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bronus Blackblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 4:06:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> My evidence was based on taking a 21 dmg weapon and comparing it to the max with a LSoEE.  The 21 base weapon had a higher max than the LSoEE, which shouldn't be true. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82998>Bronus Blackblade</a> - Assassin<br><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94791>Mystin De`Vermiis</a> - Enchanter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskoobin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skoobin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 1:21:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://skoobin5881.homestead.com/files/flcl_avie12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> i have a Johans stake of slaying which would normally if this was correct have a something like 17 damage vs vampyres but when i backstab i get my min every time... seems to me it does not add to the damage on a backstab however my pierces are MUCH higher than usual. <p><img src="http://www.ukgarageworldwide.com/images/dc.gif"><BR>Skoobin Tudrubadoobin<BR>Frayed Knot<BR>Lvl 60 Assassin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubronusblackblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bronus Blackblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 1:44:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> Most likely that is a Bane weapon, right?  Bane is added to the base, elemental and such is added after as a + from what I've seen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 2:34:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> Max damage is incredibly unreliable, the frequency you hit for max depends mostly on your atk and your opponents ac, and it never, ever gets very high.  Throw in the extra variable of resists, and you have to watch a log for a good long time to find it's true max...<br><br>Sigh...<br><br>Ok, here is a graph of my Ragebringer mainhand.  15 damage weapon, 9 damage bonus back when I made this log in December:<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://64.81.174.43/pics/pierce.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Notice the nice prominant spike at 39.  A weapon's mode is is always 2x+y, where x is the base damage, and y is the damage bonus.  Plug in the numbers and, yup, (2*15)+9=39.<br><br>Now, what does this mean for elemental damage?  Well, it either adds to the base damage or the damage bonus.  If it's a bonus, the new formula is 2x+y+z.  Plug in the numbers for a LSoEE in the offhand, and we have (2*16)+0+(0..5).  The graph would show a plateau across 32 to 37.  How high the individual peaks are within the plateau depends on the resist rate, but those six numbers should still be a fair bit above the surroundings.<br><br>If it adds to the base, it's 2*(x+z)+y.  That makes a LSoEE 2*(16+(0..5))+0, and we should see alternating peaks and valleys starting with 32 and ending with 42.<br><br>Now here's the graph of my LSoEE, offhand over the same period as the Ragebringer above.  Which equation do the peaks fit?<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://64.81.174.43/pics/slash.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 4:33:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> Dumb question ... but, well, since you hit for less than 5 in your offhand, and if it was 2*x+y+z ... and z is 5 ... well...<br><br>it seems that it wouldn't make sense to hit for less than 5 if it was just plain added to the damage.<br><br>*edit* doh, nevermind .. its a proc, doesn't always happen =)<br><br>-=Viren=-<br>40th Rogue of FV <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A> at: 3/25/02 4:49:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utiiomon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiiomon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 8:09:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tkcity.com/bbs2/kaogif/hate.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> Bane Damage: Unresistable Damage that only works on a certain type of mobs. Adds to the BASE Damage (Before-hand Damage, not After. Note: Damage Bonus is applied afterhand.)<br><br>Elemental Damage: Resistable Damage that checks against a mobs Elemental Save. Replace Elemental with Fire/Cold/Magic/Disease/Poison. Can be resisted. Adds to the BASE Damage (Before-hand Damage, not After. Note: Damage Bonus is applied afterhand.)<br>Examples:<br>A 10/22 +2 Bane Versus Gnolls would be a 10/22 versus everything, except for gnolls. It would be a 12/22.<br>A 10/22 +2 Elemental Damage Fire would be randomly a 10, 11, or 12. The mob would check versus fire. If it suceeds the check, damage is 10. If it fails the check, damage is randomly chosen 11 or 12.<br><br>and for proof, see those graphs.<br><br>Memorize those 2 definations, and spread the knowledge, my children. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kalaks>Kalaks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 4:57:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13687.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage bonuses and how they apply</span><hr size=1> For the vampire bane not working, well not everything that seems like a vampire is really tagged as a vampire by the zone designers... <p><BR>----------------------- <BR>Kalaks Kostaja - the haffer blackguard at EMarr<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=